My meme

A meme created because it was.

library(magick)

# read images for the meme
i1 <- image_read("images/thinking.jpg")
i2 <- image_read("images/blob.png")

# make images the same size
i1 <- image_scale(i1, "400")
i2 <- image_scale(i2, "400")

# add text to images
txtbox <- image_blank(color = "black", width = 400, height = 100)
i1 <- image_append(c(i1, txtbox), stack = TRUE)
i1 <- image_annotate(i1, text = "Me thinking of a\nmeme for stats220", size = 40, 
                     color = "#0000ff", gravity = "south", location = "+0+10")
i2 <- image_annotate(i2, text = "Empty\nhead", size = 40, color = "blue", 
                     gravity = "south", location = "+0+180")
i2 <- image_annotate(i2, text = "submitting this", size = 40, color = "blue", 
                     gravity = "south", location = "+0+50")


# combine images to create meme
meme <- image_append(c(i1, i2), stack = TRUE)

meme
image_write(meme, "meme.png")

My animated GIF

An animation. He’s a bird.

library(magick)

# read images for the meme
b1 <- image_read("images/b1.jpg")
b2 <- image_read("images/b2.jpg")
b3 <- image_read("images/b3.jpg")
b4 <- image_read("images/b4.jpg")

# add text to images
b1 <- image_annotate(b1, text = "I", size = 100, color = "#0000ff", gravity = "north")
b2 <- image_annotate(b2, text = "am", size = 100, color = "#0000ff", gravity = "north")
b3 <- image_annotate(b3, text = "a", size = 100, color = "#0000ff", gravity = "north")
b4 <- image_annotate(b4, text = "BIRD!", size = 100, color = "#0000ff", gravity = "north")

# make all images the same size
b1 <- image_scale(b1, 400)
b2 <- image_scale(b2, 400)
b3 <- image_scale(b3, 400)
b4 <- image_scale(b4, 400)

# put the images together
animation <- c(b1, b2, b3, b4)

# play animation
animation <- image_animate(animation, fps = 1)
animation
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
